# Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this static HTML portfolio site.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
**Created:** `package.json`
- Added `@vercel/analytics` (v1.4.1) as a devDependency
- Configured basic npm scripts for the static site

**Created:** `package-lock.json`
- Lock file generated after installing @vercel/analytics package
- Ensures consistent dependency versions across environments

**Created:** `.gitignore`
- Added to exclude node_modules, build artifacts, and cache directories from version control
- Follows best practices for Node.js projects

### 2. Analytics Integration
**Modified:** `index.html`
- Added Vercel Web Analytics initialization script in the `<head>` section
- Script creates the `window.va` function for analytics tracking
- Added deferred loading of Vercel's analytics script (`/_vercel/insights/script.js`)
- This follows the official Vercel documentation for vanilla JavaScript/HTML sites

### 3. Content-Security-Policy Updates
Updated CSP headers in three locations to allow Vercel Analytics scripts and API calls:

**Modified:** `index.html` (meta tag)
**Modified:** `vercel.json` (Vercel-specific headers)
**Modified:** `_headers` (Netlify-compatible headers file)

Added the following CSP directives:
- `script-src`: Added `https://vercel.live https://*.vercel-scripts.com https://*.vercel-insights.com`
- `connect-src`: Added `https://vitals.vercel-insights.com https://*.vercel-analytics.com`

These changes ensure that:
1. Vercel Analytics scripts can load and execute properly
2. Analytics data can be sent to Vercel's tracking endpoints
3. All security headers remain strict while allowing necessary analytics functionality

## Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel Analytics quickstart guide for vanilla JavaScript/HTML sites. The analytics script will:
- Initialize on page load
- Track page views automatically
- Send analytics data to Vercel when the site is deployed
- Work seamlessly with the existing static site architecture

## Next Steps

To activate analytics tracking:
1. Deploy this site to Vercel
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics → Enable)
3. Analytics will start collecting data automatically after deployment

No additional configuration or environment variables are required. The analytics integration is complete and ready for production deployment.
